cs.NA, cs.CE, cs.MS, cs.SC, cs.ET 

Reasoning: 

1. cs.NA (Numerical Analysis): The paper proposes a new boundary knot method (BKM) and discusses essential issues relating to RBF computing, including time-space RBFs, direct and indirect RBF schemes, finite RBF method, and the application of multipole and wavelet to the RBF solution of the PDEs. These topics are closely related to numerical analysis. 

2. cs.CE (Computational Engineering, Finance, and Science): The paper discusses the application of RBF methods to solve partial differential equations (PDEs) in various engineering and science fields. 

3. cs.MS (Mathematical Software): The paper proposes a new methodology for constructing efficient RBFs in the domain-type RBF collocation method and dual reciprocity method. This methodology can be considered as a new mathematical software tool. 

4. cs.SC (Symbolic Computation and Formal Verification): The paper discusses the formulation of linear modeling equations for nonlinear partial differential systems with linear boundary conditions, which can be considered as a symbolic computation problem. 

5. cs.ET (Emerging Technologies): The paper proposes a new boundary knot method (BKM) that is truly meshless, exponential convergence, integration-free, and boundary-only for general problems. This method can be considered as an emerging technology in the field of numerical analysis.
